*----------------------------------------------------------------------
* test/fence_function/t02_outer_alternatives.sno
* FENCE(P) failure: when P fails, FENCE(P) fails, but the enclosing
* pattern can still try its own alternatives.
* FENCE(P) failing does NOT abort the whole match (unlike &FENCE).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------
               S = 'bx'
*   ('a' | 'b') is outside the fence, so backtracking IS allowed there
               S  ('a' | 'b') FENCE('x')                   :F(FAIL)
               OUTPUT = 'PASS t02: outer alternatives work after FENCE(P) inner fail'
                                                            :(END)
FAIL           OUTPUT = 'FAIL t02: outer alternatives work after FENCE(P) inner fail'
END
